The Telegraph - Calcutta : Metro

 What We are Watching

Theatre

 Supriya Chowdhury (right) rehearses for 

Janani

 Janani

 A star-studded cast led by Supriya Chowdhury and Madhabi Mukherjee, presented by Niva Arts. The story of a joint family and the problems that arise when the structure breaks down also features small screen faces like Anuradha Roy, Sanghamitra Banerjee and Bodhisatwa Majumdar. Theatre thespian Gyanesh Mukherjee has a special role. 

Catch it at Tapan Theatre

March 19 and 20, 3 pm and 6.30 pm

 Kamla

 The Vijay Tendulkar play is a bilingual venture (Hindi and English) directed by Sheo Kr. Jhunjhunwala and presented by Proscenium. Based on the real-life experience of a journalist, the play exposes the oppression of women.

Catch it at Gyan Manch

March 19 and 26, 6.30 pm

 Nandikar rehearses for Sojon Badiyar 

Ghat 

Sojon Badiyar Ghat

 Directed by Goutam Halder, the Nandikar play is an adaptation of Jasimuddin?s verse epic on strife, war, love and death tearing apart the Hindu and Muslim communities. Folk music and rural activities, including laathi khela, are an integral part of the production.

Catch it at Rabindra Sadan 

March 18, 6 pm




